commit.message: Debian changelog for 5.5.22
Prevent a segmentation fault with --no-recursion
Update the .vi TLD server

Update the .bm TLD server

New registrar.
Remove 2 new gTLDs which are no longer active
Debian changelog for 5.5.21
Depend on pkgconf instead of pkg-config

Update the .sd TLD server

Same server, different domain.
Update the .cv TLD server
Suppress the "unused parameter" warning in get_random_bytes()
Remove 8 new gTLDs which are no longer active
Fix memory leak in whois.c
Use __attribute__((malloc(free))) only with GCC >= 11
Remove the copyright years from the sources files
Switch the documentation URLs to https
Debian changelog for 5.5.20
Add a Github workflow to automatically make releases
Enable getopt_long(3) support on Solaris
Remove 6 new gTLDs which are no longer active
Add the .gn TLD server
Use __attribute__((unused))

Do not use __attribute__((malloc(free))) with Clang

This extension is not implemented by Clang.

Refactoring

Merge the as and as32 data structures, since it is highly unlikely
that using short ints will save any memory.
Debian changelog for 5.5.19
Update the pl translation

Update the charset for whois.jprs.jp

whois.jprs.jp switched to UTF-8 on January 18, 2015:
https://jprs.jp/whatsnew/notice/2014/20140319-whois.html .
mkpasswd: prevent using two unitialized variables

Annotate do_nofail() with malloc(free) and returns_nonnull

Or else the compiler will be unable to understand that the NOFAIL()
macro never returns a NULL pointer.

Do not add again the /e argument to Japanese queries

The /e argument should not be added if it has already been provided by
the user.

Closes: #1050171
Refactor the code which detects the ASN names
